                       Installation procedures
                       -----------------------

======================================================================
A. Installation on Unix
======================================================================

In the following it is assumed that Python is already running on your
system. If you are not sure, type

> python

to start the interpreter. If you get the Python commandline,
everything is ok. Leave Python with the key Ctrl-D. If you get an
error message instead, You will have to install python on your system
first. If python is not part of your system distribution then take it
from http://www.python.org.


1. Set PYTHONPATH
-----------------

In your shell type:

> cat >> $HOME/.profile << EOF
> PH=$HOME/lib/python
> export PYTHONPATH=$PH/Spectrum:$PH/Lanthanide:$PH/Fiblas
> EOF
> . $HOME/.profile


2. Install Numeric Python
-------------------------

Get the source package (e.g. Numeric-21.3.tar.gz) from
http://www.numpy.org and save to $HOME/src. Then type in your shell:

> cd $HOME/src
> tar xzf ~/Numeric-*.tar.gz
> cd Numeric-*
> python setup.py build
> su root
> python setup.py install


3. Install Scientific Python
----------------------------

Get the source package (e.g. ScientificPython-3.4.1.tar.gz) from
http://dirac.cnrs-orleans.fr/ScientificPython and save it to
$HOME/src. Then type in your shell:

> cd $HOME/src
> tar xzf ScientificPython-*.tar.gz
> cd ScientificPython-*
> python setup.py build
> su root
> python setup.py install


4. Install the BLAS and LAPACK libraries
----------------------------------------

Get the source package lapack.tgz from http://www.netlib.org/lapack
and save it to $HOME/src. Then type in your shell:

> cd $HOME/src
> tar xzf lapack.tgz
> cd LAPACK

Take the appropriate make.inc from the directory INSTALL. In case of a
Linux system e.g. type:

> cp INSTALL/make.inc.LINUX make.inc
> make blaslib
> make lapacklib
> su root
> cp blas_LINUX.a /usr/lib/libblas.a
> cp lapack_LINUX.a /usr/lib/liblapack.a


5. Install Spectrum
-------------------

Copy the Spectrum package (e.g. Spectrum-0.2.tar.gz) to
$HOME/src. Then type in your shell:

> cd $HOME/src
> tar xzf Spectrum-*.tar.gz
> cd Spectrum-*
> python setup.py install

To test the package type (see README for more info):

> cd test
> python test.py


6. Install Lanthanide
---------------------

Copy the Lanthanide package (e.g. Lanthanide-0.2.tar.gz) to
$HOME/src. Then type in your shell:

> cd $HOME/src
> tar xzf Lanthanide-*.tar.gz
> cd Lanthanide-*
> python setup.py install

To test the package type (see README for more info):

> cd test
> python test.py


5. Install Fiblas
-----------------

Copy the Fiblas package (e.g. Fiblas-0.2.tar.gz) to
$HOME/src. Then type in your shell:

> cd $HOME/src
> tar xzf Fiblas-*.tar.gz
> cd Fiblas-*
> python setup.py install

To test the package type (see README for more info):

> cd test
> python test.py



======================================================================
B. Installation on Microsoft Windows
======================================================================

1. Install the cygwin environment
---------------------------------

Go to http://www.cygwin.com and run the installer program setup.exe on
this page. In addition to the default selection install at least the
following components:

  Devel - gcc
  Devel - make
  Interpreters - python

Then start the cygwin shell (bash) and type:

> cat >> ~/.bashrc << EOF
> PH=$HOME/lib/python
> export PYTHONPATH=$PH/Spectrum:$PH/Lanthanide:$PH/Fiblas
> EOF
> exit

Start the cygwin shell again.


2. Install Numeric Python
-------------------------

Get the source package (e.g. Numeric-21.3.tar.gz) from
http://www.numpy.org and save it to C:\cygwin\usr\src. In the cygwin
shell type:

> cd /usr/src
> tar xzf Numeric-*.tar.gz
> cd Numeric-*
> python setup.py install


3. Install Scientific Python
----------------------------

Get the source package (e.g. ScientificPython-3.4.1.tar.gz) from
http://dirac.cnrs-orleans.fr/ScientificPython and save it to
C:\cygwin\usr\src. In the cygwin shell type:

> cd /usr/src
> tar xzf ScientificPython-*.tar.gz
> cd ScientificPython-*
> python setup.py install


4. Install the BLAS and LAPACK libraries
----------------------------------------

Get the source package lapack.tgz from http://www.netlib.org/lapack
and save it to C:\cygwin\usr\src. In the cygwin shell type:

> cd /usr/src
> tar xzf lapack.tgz
> cd LAPACK
> cp INSTALL/make.inc.LINUX make.inc
> make blaslib
> make lapacklib
> cp blas_LINUX.a /usr/lib/libblas.a
> cp lapack_LINUX.a /usr/lib/liblapack.a


5. Install Spectrum
-------------------

Copy the Spectrum package (e.g. Spectrum-0.2.tar.gz) to
C:\cygwin\usr\src. In the cygwin shell type:

> cd /usr/src
> tar xzf Spectrum-*.tar.gz
> cd Spectrum-*
> python setup.py install

To test the package type (see README for more info):

> cd test
> python test.py


6. Install Lanthanide
---------------------

Copy the Lanthanide package (e.g. Lanthanide-0.2.tar.gz) to
C:\cygwin\usr\src. In the cygwin shell type:

> cd /usr/src
> tar xzf Lanthanide-*.tar.gz
> cd Lanthanide-*
> python setup.py install

To test the package type (see README for more info):

> cd test
> python test.py


5. Install Fiblas
-----------------

Copy the Fiblas package (e.g. Fiblas-0.2.tar.gz) to
C:\cygwin\usr\src. In the cygwin shell type:

> cd /usr/src
> tar xzf Fiblas-*.tar.gz
> cd Fiblas-*
> python setup.py install

To test the package type (see README for more info):

> cd test
> python test.py


That's it. Have fun!
